'''Jacques Vriens''' (born 26 March 1946) is a Dutch children's author and playwright.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jacques Vriens: 'Leerkracht moet zich ontworstelen aan afrekencultuur overheid'|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/3184/opinie/article/detail/3513238/2013/09/21/Jacques-Vriens-Leerkracht-moet-zich-ontworstelen-aan-afrekencultuur-overheid.dhtml|publisher=Volkskrant|accessdate=4 May 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505111212/http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/3184/opinie/article/detail/3513238/2013/09/21/Jacques-Vriens-Leerkracht-moet-zich-ontworstelen-aan-afrekencultuur-overheid.dhtml|archivedate=5 May 2014|df=}}</ref> He is known for his 1999 book ''[[Achtste-groepers huilen niet]]'', which was adapted twice into film. Vriens formerly worked as a schoolteacher and has written for the show ''Tien torens diep''. In 2001 he was appointed to the [[Order of the Netherlands Lion]] by former [[Queen Beatrix|Queen Beatrix of the Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Koningin beloont Carrell en Brusse|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2844/Archief/archief/article/detail/601642/2001/04/28/Koningin-beloont-Carrell-en-Brusse.dhtml|publisher=Volkskrant|accessdate=4 May 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505111208/http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2844/Archief/archief/article/detail/601642/2001/04/28/Koningin-beloont-Carrell-en-Brusse.dhtml|archivedate=5 May 2014|df=}}</ref>

==Works adapted==
* ''[[Tien torens diep]]'' (''Ten Towers Deep'') (2004 book;<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.goodreads.com/work/editions/16099635-tien-torens-diep|date=1999|title=Tien torens diep|edition=Hardcover|author=Vriens, Jacques|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810222029/https://www.goodreads.com/work/editions/16099635-tien-torens-diep|archivedate=2017-08-10|df=}}</ref> 2009 television series<ref>{{cite book|title=Tien torens diep|date=1999|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1515685/|edition=TV series|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170210214441/http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1515685/|archivedate=2017-02-10|df=}}</ref>)
* ''[[Achtste-groepers huilen niet]]'' (''Eighth Graders Don't Cry'', ''Kule Kidz Gråter Ikke'', ''Cool Kids Don't Cry'') (1999 book;<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8050771-achtste-groepers-huilen-niet|date=1999|title=Achtste-groepers huilen niet|edition=Hardcover|author=Vriens, Jacques|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902090851/https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8050771-achtste-groepers-huilen-niet|archivedate=2014-09-02|df=}}</ref> 2012 film;<ref>{{cite book|title=Cool Kids Don't Cry|date=February 15, 2012|location=Netherlands|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1800372/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1}}</ref> 2014 film<ref>{{cite book|title=Cool Kids Don't Cry|date=January 10, 2014|location=Norway|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2865618/?ref_=tt_trv_cnn|edition=Film}}</ref>)
* ''[[Oorlogsgeheimen]]'' (''Secrets of War'') (2007 book;<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.goodreads.com/work/editions/16595884-oorlogsgeheimen|date=2007|title=Oorlogsgeheimen|author=Vriens, Jacques|edition=Film|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810232552/https://www.goodreads.com/work/editions/16595884-oorlogsgeheimen|archivedate=2017-08-10|df=}}</ref> 2014 film<ref>{{cite book|title=Oorlogsgeheimen|date=July 3, 2014|location=Netherlands|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2371158/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1|edition=Film|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160113013425/http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2371158/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1|archivedate=January 13, 2016|df=}}</ref>)

